args: Grant me now the glory of thy name.

Make me as your readied instrument of
salvation before all. Grant thy vast and
holy radiance, that all darkness here be
banished!
A sylvan village in North Grastaea
It looks as though the purification is\ncomplete, Nevin.
Purification, huh? Considering the sorry\nstate of things, I can't help but get a pretty\nstrong sense that we're too little, too late.
I empathize with your regret that\nwe could not save these people.
Given our thin numbers, though, this\nsort of outcome was unavoidable.
Hrk... Our village!\nWhy did this have to happen...?
Hey! We've got a live one, Ramiel!
He looks wounded in places, but\nthankfully, he yet draws breath.
What?! You're the one from last night!\nNo way. Why are you back?!
Yeah, I know.\nIt means we've got trouble.
North Grastaea\nA village on the outskirts of the Holy City Grams
I can sense an ominous miasma issuing\nforth from inside the village.
It's just like those poor folks told us.

Y'know, I really thought all that stuff about
an angel of the Ilian Church gathering up
villagers and havin' some wild party was a
buncha cock-and-bull, but here we are.

We've yet to ascertain the identity of the
perpetrator, Ranzal. For now, our first
priority is to save the village. We must
excise the source of this miasma.
Huh? Wait, everyone!\nThere's something strange afoot.
Are these the locals?\nThis lady's kinda—
Whoa, whoa! Not good!\nShe's lost her marbles!
We cannot harm innocents. Let us avoid\nthem and find from whence the miasma\nstems!
Hang on, kiddo.\nLet a pro handle this.

If you wanna get through these folks
without hurting 'em, you just leave it up
to Papa Bear. First I'll give 'em a little
spritz of sanctified water, like so...

Grant me now the glory of thy name.
Make me as your readied instrument of
salvation before all, and give unto your
consecrated their perfect repose!
All the nearby miasma has disappeared!\nIncredible.

Sure has, but it's just a temporary thing.
So long as we don't cut off whatever's
actually causing the stuff to show up,
we'll be right back in the same pickle.
In any case, we're grateful for your help.\nWhy are you here, though, Nevin?
Same reason you are. We Church folks\nalso want to avoid any undue bad press\nfor our angels.
Guess that means all the rumors and\nhearsay about an angel really are just that.
If only it were that simple.

One pair of eyes on a situation is better
than a hundred mouths talking about it.
It'd be faster to just get a look at
whatever's causing the outbreak ourselves.
An aerial view suggests that the miasma\nis billowing forth from a chapel at the\ncenter of the village.
Well, that's pretty ideal. All righty—\nshall we go sort the problem out?
Ngh... No ordinary person could withstand\nsuch a fierce concentration of miasma.

They would lose all sense of reason in
under ten seconds. Anyone lacking the
divine protection of holy mana would fall
within ten minutes. That includes you.
Do my eyes deceive me? That looks like...
So it does. I expected as much, given\nwhat we heard of the situation from those\nwho survived, but...
Our mana resonates. You have come at\nlast. I bid myself welcome, Ramiel.
You've made quite a nuisance of yourself,\nslithering around with my appearance.\nThe mere thought of it disgusts me.

So basically, he's taken on Ramiel's
appearance to trick the people, and then
gone around the villages near Grams
to suffuse them all with miasma...
So is he the same as the last demon\nwe fought?

Ha ha. What you fought was but a pale
imitation wrought from the miasma that
spilled from a sealing stone. In other
words, a pseudo-demon.
Quite. And it is most displeasing to\nbe underestimated by rabble like you.\nI shall have to revise your perception.
For the power of the Five Archdemons is\nfar and away greater than you imagine!
Tch. This thing's on a whole different level\nthan the bastard we fought before. You\nready to tango, {player_name}?

Our enemy's power may be immeasurable,
but if we don't defeat him, we cannot undo
the harm caused by the miasma.
We have to stop him here!

Indeed. Were we to turn a blind eye, the
ensuing miasmic mayhem would only grow
to encompass all of North Grastaea—nay,
the whole of the world.
And all those afflicted would coalesce into\na violent mob bereft of reason. It is not\nsomething that we can let come to pass.
Guess I'd better clock in for real on\nthis one, then. I, the apostle Nevin,\nshall administer Her will!

Angels and humans both... You never
change, no matter how many hundreds
of years pass. The way you swarm like
insects is enough to make me sick.

And insects should behave as such:
abandon your reason, and be smeared
in dirt as you grovel upon the earth!
The hour of your extermination is nigh!
